  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nIf you add an emoji reaction to the last message of a channel at the bottom, you can't see the reaction until you scroll, so it looks like it didn't work.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to a channel with messages or add one yourself\r\n2. Scroll all the way down\r\n3. Add a reaction to the last message\r\nResult: can't see it\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe chat scrolls down so we stay at the bottom\r\n\r\nThe simple way of doing it is to force a scroll down when sending the reaction.\r\nThe (maybe) harder way, but the best way, would be to enforce that if we are at the bottom of the chat, it should stick there, so if there are new messages from anyone, we stay at the botom (like a magnet)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
